  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bc1 \u0b8e\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc6\u0bbe\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3 \u0ba8\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0ba9\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc6\u0bbe\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc2\u0bb1\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0b9a\u0baa\u0bbe\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0baf\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Everyone should be responsible for the crisis facing the country - Speaker",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "Priority should be given to matters that benefit the people rather than giving too much prominence to unnecessary speeches made in Parliament.",
        "And everyone must be held accountable for the crisis facing the country. Speaker Mahinda Yapa Abeywardena said the issue would not be resolved if the culprits were found and punished.",
        "A special seminar for Parliamentary journalists was held today at the Cinnamon Grand Hotel, Colombo. He said this while addressing a special guest function there.",
        "The seminar was attended by a number of dignitaries, including the Parliamentary Secretary General, as well as journalists from the print media and electronic media companies.",
        "What is the next step if the people say no to the 225 members of parliament? What happened when the cabinet was dissolved and the prime minister was ousted? Have you got everything you need? At the same time, what happened when a new Prime Minister was appointed and a new Cabinet was appointed? Have you got fuel or have you got the essentials? What's next?",
        "If parliament is dissolved and re-elected, 225 people will return. Will everything be alright then? So should we throw away the constitution? We must fulfill our responsibility to the people and protect it. We need to think about the country and future generations. It is necessary to win the confidence of the people in connection with Parliament.",
        "The new government will be formed and the newcomers will do the same and leave. We have to live in that situation.",
        "Our children must live. Schools were continuously closed even in the corona situation. Schools are still closed again Where are we going ?.",
        "At the same time, it is the responsibility of the media to make it clear to the public that they are facing great inconvenience for their own needs.",
        "They should not be given prominence. It is only when it is so provided that the country becomes confused and the people become confused.",
        "So people will say no to 225 people. The next step is to give the property what the house is on fire for. If so what is the next step?",
        "During my tenure in 1983, 14 MPs were assassinated. The houses of 80 MPs have been burnt down. My house also burned down. Only the baby's milk bottle was left over. If so what is the next step?",
        "The constitution is the basis of everything in the country. The constitution must be protected and the democracy of this country must be protected. Our duty may be over but democracy must be protected.",
        "We are afraid of the democracy we have to defend. There is something wrong with everyone. That mistake must be changed to help the progress of the country and society.",
        "Parliamentary journalists have a great responsibility. Has a responsibility to protect the country. Political leaders are not one hundred percent right and some are right.",
        "Not just here, but anywhere in the world. That is what we need to do to strengthen and encourage those who do more good.",
        "It is necessary to point out mistakes. Our economic downturn did not come yesterday. Did those responsible for it take action? Or will punishing them solve the problems? So what is the solution to the crisis? Is it okay if he is meeting to be held accountable? He therefore said that the media should take the responsibility of providing proper information to the people and bringing them into the democratic stream."
      ],
